, Julus Antonius was the son of the Triumvir by Fulvia, and was educated by his step-mother Octavia. Through her protection he was spared when his brother Marcus Antyllus was stain. and rose eventually to high favour with Augustus, and was married to Marcella, Octavia's daughter, aster her divorce from Agrippa in ac. 21. Horace’s Ode is the only ancient authority for his having been a poet; but the Pseudo-Acron vouches for his having written an excellent Epic poem in twelve Douka, called the Diomedem, some years afterwards. He was made praetor ina.c.13‚and consul in rac. ro. In ac. 2 he was condemned to death on the charge of adulterans intercourse with Julia.
